SEMDL Help Topic: reference similarity

Usage:
- `ssd similarity <id> <id> <file>`

Behavior:
- Compare two existing semantic targets in one input document using precomputed embeddings only.
- The current slice uses cosine similarity and requires matching model and dimensions.
- Both inline `vector` and external `vector_ref` embedding records are supported.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help troubleshooting`
